<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-11-21T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-11-21T16:00:00-05:00" n="591" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d591">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11 <persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_EH1">Ekvall, Henry</persName>/62:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China (<persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_JNT1" type="to">Johnson</persName>)</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-21T16:00:00-05:00">November 21, 1932—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>372. Your 1254, November 17, 1 p.m., and previous. For your information
                            and encouragement, the Department has suggested to the Chinese Legation
                            here that it inform Nanking that the Department is emphatically
                            interested in and solicitous with regard to this case and that matters
                            relating to this case are being pressed by our representatives in China
                            under express instruction from the Department.</p>
                        <closer><signed><persName corresp="frus1932v03#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>